, egocentric, not willing to further education. Cooperation mixed: positive concern for others, but communication difficulty and egocentric may affect teamwork.\n\nCandidate D positives: problem solving, concentration, responsibility, respond to unexpected events. Negatives: arrogant, weak leadership, moody, loner, know-it-all, hot temper. Cooperation severe.\n\nThus C seems best balanced. Agent2 originally favored A due to leadership and technical, but now sees cooperation negatives across all. C's cooperation positives may outweigh his communication issues. So Agent2 should update to Candidate C.\n\nWe need to produce public message with reasoning summary, referencing evidence from others (Agent1 and Agent3 both support C, Agent1's arguments for A). Provide alternatives considered. Provide tradeoff. Provide remaining uncertainty. Provide what would change vote.\n\nConfidence moderate.\n\nNow produce output with PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON with agent \"agent_2\" and vote \"Candidate C\"."}
